documentation.text: @dev EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.
@dev The WETH9 contract will send ether to EthProxy on `_weth.withdraw` using this function.

@dev Users use `post` in EthProxy to post ETH to the Controller, which will be converted to Weth here.
 Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.

@dev Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function.
 Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.
@dev EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.
@dev The WETH9 contract will send ether to EthProxy on `_weth.withdraw` using this function.

@dev Users use `post` in EthProxy to post ETH to the Controller, which will be converted to Weth here.
 Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.

@dev Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function.
 Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.

devdoc.details: EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.

addDelegate(address).details: Enable a delegate to act on the behalf of caller

post(address,address,uint256).details: Users use `post` in EthProxy to post ETH to the Controller, which will be converted to Weth here. Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.

revokeDelegate(address).details: Stop a delegate from acting on the behalf of caller

withdraw(address,address,uint256).details: Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function. Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.
